                    <fr:route>jms-00NB.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Disjoint unions of enumerable sets">Disjoint unions of enumerable sets</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Proposition</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable set</fr:link> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-00N9.xml" title="Family of sets" addr="jms-00N9" type="local">family of sets</fr:link> indexed in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> such that each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_i]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>. Then the disjoint union <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A = \coprod _{i\in  I}A_i]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7709</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6087</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6087.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>By assumption, we have an <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumeration</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_I\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  I]]></fr:tex>; as each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A_i]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumerable</fr:link>, we may use the <fr:link href="jms-00MM.xml" title="The axiom of choice" addr="jms-00MM" type="local">axiom of choice</fr:link> to assign to each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\in  I]]></fr:tex> a specific <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_i\colon  \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow  A_i]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon \mathbb {N}\twoheadrightarrow \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> be any <fr:link href="jms-00ME.xml" title="Enumerable set" addr="jms-00ME" type="local">enumeration</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex>. Define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k\colon \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}\to  A]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  k{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}} = e_{e_I{\mathopen {}\left (m\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>The function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k\colon \mathbb {N}\times \mathbb {N}\to  A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>: fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  A]]></fr:tex>, we must find <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i=\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>; because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_I]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>, we may find <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_I{\mathopen {}\left (m\right )\mathclose {}}=\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>, and because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}}]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjective</fr:link>, we may find <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n\in  \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}} = a]]></fr:tex>.</html:span> Therefore, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k{\mathopen {}\left (m,n\right )\mathclose {}} = e_{e_I{\mathopen {}\left (m\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}} = e_{\pi _A{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (n\right )\mathclose {}}=a]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
