                <fr:route>jms-016E.xml</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Fixed point theorems">Fixed point theorems</fr:title>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                      <fr:contributor>
                        <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
                      </fr:contributor>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>31</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>7712</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="user">jms-00NG</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>jms-00NG.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Fixed point">Fixed point</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>A <fr:em><fr:strong>fixed point</fr:strong></fr:em> of a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  X]]></fr:tex> is an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  X]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}=x]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                      <fr:contributor>
                        <fr:link href="marcelofiore.xml" title="Marcelo Fiore" addr="marcelofiore" type="local">Marcelo Fiore</fr:link>
                      </fr:contributor>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>31</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>7713</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="user">jms-00NH</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>jms-00NH.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Lawvere’s fixed point theorem">Lawvere’s fixed point theorem</fr:title>
                    <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Given sets <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, if there exists a <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\twoheadrightarrow {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  X\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> then every function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X\to  X]]></fr:tex> has a <fr:link href="jms-00NG.xml" title="Fixed point" addr="jms-00NG" type="local">fixed point</fr:link>; and hence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a singleton.</fr:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>7327</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">unstable/6089</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-6089.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  X\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link>.
 Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  X]]></fr:tex> be a function of which are trying to find a <fr:link href="jms-00NG.xml" title="Fixed point" addr="jms-00NG" type="local">fixed point</fr:link>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[h\colon  A\to  X]]></fr:tex> be the following function:</fr:p>

 <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  h{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}} = f{\mathopen {}\left (e{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}
 ]]></fr:tex>

 <fr:p>Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  X\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-00M8.xml" title="Surjection" addr="jms-00M8" type="local">surjection</fr:link>, we may find <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a_h\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}} = h]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}} = f{\mathopen {}\left (e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> and so <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}{\mathopen {}\left (a_h\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="jms-00NG.xml" title="Fixed point" addr="jms-00NG" type="local">fixed point</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>Finally, we conclude that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is a singleton: first of all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> has at least one element (the fixed point of the identity function). Now, let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0\not = x_1\in  X]]></fr:tex> be two unequal elements of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> and let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  X\to  X]]></fr:tex> be the function that sends <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_1]]></fr:tex> and everything else to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0]]></fr:tex>. By assumption, we have a fixed point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\in  X]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. We now proceed by cases:</fr:p>
 <fr:ol><fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p=x_0]]></fr:tex>, then we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=x_1]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=p]]></fr:tex> and thus <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0=x_1]]></fr:tex>, a contradiction.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p\not = x_0]]></fr:tex>, then we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=x_0]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f{\mathopen {}\left (p\right )\mathclose {}}=p]]></fr:tex>, also a contradiction.</fr:li></fr:ol>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
                <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
                  <fr:frontmatter>
                    <fr:authors>
                      <fr:author>
                        <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
                      </fr:author>
                    </fr:authors>
                    <fr:date>
                      <fr:year>2024</fr:year>
                      <fr:month>1</fr:month>
                      <fr:day>31</fr:day>
                    </fr:date>
                    <fr:anchor>7714</fr:anchor>
                    <fr:addr type="user">jms-00NI</fr:addr>
                    <fr:route>jms-00NI.xml</fr:route>
                    <fr:title text="Deducing Cantor’s theorem à la Lawvere">Deducing <fr:link href="jms-00NF.xml" title="Cantor’s theorem" addr="jms-00NF" type="local">Cantor’s theorem</fr:link> à la <fr:link href="jms-00NH.xml" title="Lawvere’s fixed point theorem" addr="jms-00NH" type="local">Lawvere</fr:link></fr:title>
                  </fr:frontmatter>
                  <fr:mainmatter>
                    <fr:p>To deduce <fr:link href="jms-00NF.xml" title="Cantor’s theorem" addr="jms-00NF" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00NF" /></fr:link> from <fr:link href="jms-00NH.xml" title="Lawvere’s fixed point theorem" addr="jms-00NH" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00NH" /></fr:link>, we suppose that there is a surjection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A\twoheadrightarrow  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (A\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>; by <fr:link href="jms-00LN.xml" title="Universal property of indicator functions" addr="jms-00LN" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00LN" /></fr:link>, this is equivalent to saying that we have a surjection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e\colon  A\twoheadrightarrow  {\mathopen {}\left (A\to  {\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. From <fr:link href="jms-00NH.xml" title="Lawvere’s fixed point theorem" addr="jms-00NH" type="local">Theorem <fr:contextual-number addr="jms-00NH" /></fr:link>, it follows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left  [2\right  ]\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is a singleton — a contradiction.</fr:p>
                  </fr:mainmatter>
                </fr:tree>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
