      </fr:frontmatter>
      <fr:mainmatter>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>12</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:anchor>21873</fr:anchor>
            <fr:addr type="user">jms-017T</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>jms-017T.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="Subset construction">Subset construction</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="jms-017O.xml" title="Non-deterministic finite automaton with \varepsilon-transitions" addr="jms-017O" type="local">NFA<html:sup xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex></html:sup></fr:link> over an <fr:link href="jms-016H.xml" title="Alphabet" addr="jms-016H" type="local">alphabet</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>; we define an <fr:link href="jms-017L.xml" title="Deterministic finite automaton" addr="jms-017L" type="local">DFA</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> called the <fr:em><fr:strong>subset construction</fr:strong></fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> as follows:</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li>We define the set of states of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> to be the powerset of the set of states of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>.
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[Q_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}} = \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (Q_{M}\right )\mathclose {}} = {\mathopen {}\left \{S\,\middle \vert \,S\subseteq  Q_{M}\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>

 <fr:li>The transition function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}\colon  \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (Q_{M}\right )\mathclose {}} \times \Sigma \to \mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (Q_{M}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is so that a set of states <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> transitions along the symbol <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  \Sigma ]]></fr:tex> to the set of states reachable via <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> from <fr:em>some</fr:em> element of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   \delta _{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}}{\mathopen {}\left (S,a\right )\mathclose {}} =
   {\mathopen {}\left \{
    q'\in Q_{M}
   \,\middle \vert \,
    \exists  q\in  S\mathpunct {.}
    q\mathrel {\xRightarrow {a}} q' \text { in } M
   \right \}\mathclose {}}
  ]]></fr:tex>

  (Optional observation: this is a <fr:link href="jms-00NC.xml" title="Relational images" addr="jms-00NC" type="local">relational direct image</fr:link>.)</fr:li>

 <fr:li>The starting state of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is the set of states reachable by any number of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\varepsilon ]]></fr:tex>-transitions from the starting state of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>, i.e. the set of states reachable from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s_{M}]]></fr:tex> via the empty <fr:link href="jms-016I.xml" title="String over an alphabet" addr="jms-016I" type="local">string</fr:link>:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[s_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}} = {\mathopen {}\left \{q\in  Q\,\middle \vert \,s_{M}\mathrel {\xRightarrow {\epsilon }}q\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex></fr:li>

 <fr:li>An accepting set of states is one that contains an accepting state from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>:
  <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
   F_{\mathcal {P}{\mathopen {}\left (M\right )\mathclose {}}} =
   {\mathopen {}\left \{S\subseteq Q_{M}\,\middle \vert \,
    \exists  q\in  S\mathpunct {.}
    q\in F_{M}
   \right \}\mathclose {}}
  ]]></fr:tex></fr:li></fr:ol>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
    </fr:tree>
